This paper discusses the practical implementation of explainable machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study also explores how organizations use explainability for stakeholder consumption, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of current explainability techniques, which could be relevant to the category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CY) as well.
